Be it enacted by the Council as follows:


      Section 1. Section 14-150 of the administrative code of the city of New York is amended by adding new subdivision g to read as follows:
      g. Reporting on confirmed firearm discharges. 1. For purposes of this subdivision, the term "confirmed firearm discharge" means a firearm discharge, by any person other than a member of the department acting within the scope of their duties, that the department can corroborate with evidence recovered at the scene of the firearm discharge. Such evidence may include, but need not be limited to:
      (a) Ballistics;
      (b) Property damage;
      (c) Shell casings;
      (d) Live ammunition;
      (e) Recovered firearms;
      (f) Video;
      (g) Firsthand witness accounts; and
      (h) Victims.
      2. The department shall, on a weekly basis, report on the number of confirmed firearm discharges. Such report shall include:
      (a) The total number of confirmed firearm discharges, disaggregated by borough and by precinct;
      (b) The approximate date, time, and location for each confirmed firearm discharge; and
      (c) A description of the circumstances under which the firearms were discharged.
      � 2. This local law takes effect 120 days after it becomes law.


